      "name": "Bench-top hemolysis index comparison — FDA generic pump",
      "description": "CFD-predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) compared against published FDA bench-top measurements across 5 operating points (2–6 L/min, 2000–3500 RPM). Mean relative error 8.3%; all predictions within experimental uncertainty bands. Turbulence model performance at low-shear near-wall regions was not fully characterized for impeller geometries with volute-to-blade clearances below 0.3 mm. This edge case was not covered in the validation sweep and represents a known limitation of the current assessment."
